  <div class="container">
    
    <div class="section-header">
    
      
        
        <h2 class="title text-center">What is S.A.F.E EMDR?</h2>
        
      
      
    </div><!-- end section header -->
    

    <div class="content section-content">
      <div class="d-flex align-items-center justify-content-around row">
<div class="col-sm-10 col-md-8 col-lg-6">
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Somatic and Attachment focused EMDR is the same protocol as EMDR, there are a few added components however to increase attunement to physiological experiences as well as attachment experiences that can take place in the room. Deborah Kennard who trained under Francine Shapiro the founder of EMDR realized there were some ways to make the EMDR process within the room feel more comfortable, safe and mindful and the therapist more aware, relational and empathetic.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
</div>
<div class="col-12 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-around" style="margin-top: 1.5em;"><a href="https://www.emdr-training.net/somatic-attachment-focused-s-f-e-emdr-different" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><button class="request-button">Learn More About S.A.F.E. EMDR</button></a></div>
